						<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.rolfje.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>rolfje</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://rolfje.wordpress.com/2008/09/07/a-bigger-timemachine-without-changing-history/#comment-588">
			Wednesday 2009-02-25 at 17:08 \17\Feb\UTC +0000</a>		</div>

		<p>I&#8217;m not 100% sure, but &#8220;Time Out&#8221; seems like a different problem. Maybe you should try to just format the 1TB drive and see how that goes. If that also reasults in a timeout, you may have a faulty drive.</p>
<p>You can also try to format the drive on a different machine, at a friends house.</p>
<p>If that doesn&#8217;t work, and you&#8217;re sure that the drive is working correctly, you can try reading the Apple support forums, or calling the Apple support desk.</p>

