		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://rolfje.wordpress.com/2008/09/07/a-bigger-timemachine-without-changing-history/#comment-911">
			Thursday 2010-02-25 at 15:17 \15\Feb\UTC +0000</a>		</div>

		<p>Above (Friday 2009-12-25) I mentioned Apple&#8217;s new instructions at <a href="http://support.apple.com/kb/HT1427" rel="nofollow">http://support.apple.com/kb/HT1427</a> Today, someone reminded me about the hard links being copied as files rather than links. So, maybe the copy process has been improved in 10.6, or maybe Apple&#8217;s instructions only work when really dragging the folder in Finder (rather than using Terminal).</p>
<p>As for hard links: see also TimeCopy at <a href="http://code.google.com/p/timedog/wiki/UsingTimecopy" rel="nofollow">http://code.google.com/p/timedog/wiki/UsingTimecopy</a></p>

