						<cite class="fn">Gus Schlachter</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://rolfje.wordpress.com/2008/09/07/a-bigger-timemachine-without-changing-history/#comment-925">
			Thursday 2010-03-25 at 16:48 \16\Mar\UTC +0000</a>		</div>

		<p>P.S.  I take it back: the old inode numbers are preserved, since they are inodes within the disk image, not inodes on the physical filesystem.</p>

