		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://rolfje.wordpress.com/2008/09/07/a-bigger-timemachine-without-changing-history/#comment-1069">
			Wednesday 2010-10-27 at 19:24 \19\Oct\UTC +0000</a>		</div>

		<p>When duplicating, the Disk Utility unmounts the drive so that it can access it without other processes touching it, so that&#8217;s normal.</p>
<p>Getting your Time Machine drive to be available over the network is a whole different ballgame. You might want to start <a href="http://discussions.apple.com/message.jspa?messageID=6451729" rel="nofollow">here</a> but you didn&#8217;t hear it from me. It&#8217;s tricky stuff I haven&#8217;t figured out yet.</p>

