		<p>Wow, I never realized before that I could ask Disk Utility to &#8220;restore&#8221; directly from another disk or partition &#8211; I assumed one has to create an image file first. I even went to length to write an article in which I describe how to copy a partition using another tool in order to avoid the interim img file (<a href="http://www.tempel.org/TransferTimeMachineVolumeToLargerDisk" rel="nofollow">http://www.tempel.org/TransferTimeMachineVolumeToLargerDisk</a>). And then, after posting it on MacOSXHints, I learned it was all much simpler than I thought. Oh well, making too many assumptions is never the best way to solve a problem, and googling is always the first step to try. So, thanks for YOUR post!</p>

